Title: Title: Chicken Spinach and Black Bean Stir-Fry
Ingredients: Ingredients: - 2 tablespoons olive oil - 1 pound chicken, diced into cubes - 1 can black beans, drained - 2 cups spinach, chopped - 1 cup diced tomatoes
Instructions: Instructions: 1. Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. 2. Add the chicken cubes to the skillet and cook until golden brown, about 8 minutes. 3. Add the black beans and tomatoes and cook for an additional 5 minutes. 4. Add the spinach and stir to combine. 5. Cook until the spinach is wilted, about 3-4 minutes. 6. Serve and enjoy. Preparation time: 16 minutes

Title: Title: Noodle Lunch Bowl
Ingredients: Ingredients: - 1/2 pound noodles - 2 carrots, peeled and chopped - 2 cups shredded cabbage - 2 cloves garlic, minced
Instructions: Instructions: 1. In a large pot, bring 6-8 cups of water to a boil. 2. Once boiling, add the noodles and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. 3. Add the carrots to the pot and cook for 3 minutes. 4. 2 minutes before the noodles are finished, add the cabbage and garlic. 5. Drain the noodles after 10 minutes, and season with salt and pepper to taste. Preparation
